The paper deals with the existence of a certain function for a random variable, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of the de Bruijn's identity suggests a connection to stochastic integration (cs.SI) and the study of random processes. The definition of the set $\mathcal{L}$ and the use of the $\ln(1+|U|)$ function suggest a connection to probability theory and statistics (cs.DS), while the use of the $\mathcal{S}(\alpha;1)$ distribution suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
